This paper deals with the problem of finding the shortest sequence of operations to transform a dataset to a subsequent version, which is a common problem in database management systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes algorithms and characterizes the problem based on different constraints, which involves computational complexity and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with software engineering aspects such as scripting and modification, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a theory and provides complexity classification, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
